This paper proposes a method for deriving event storylines using multimodal data and imitation learning. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.CL and cs.LG sub-categories. The proposed method also involves generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are commonly used in the cs.AI and cs.CV sub-categories. Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of information overload, which is relevant to the cs.IR sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.IR.
